    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "One case to cover that I was just discussing with @emhane\r\n\r\nWe need to remember whether a separate blob freezer is in use and ensure that this continues to be the case. I.e. if a user has their blobs separate we record that in the hot DB and error on start-up if no separate freezer is provided. Conversely if a user _doesn't_ have a separate blob freezer we record _that_ on disk and error if they try to provide one. I think a `bool` in `BlobInfo` should do it.\r\n\r\nLater on we can implement clever things like copying between DBs, if that proves desirable. I suspect some users will also be happy with the existing hot/freezer split for managing storage (e.g. you could move your freezer to a slower drive before 4844 and then when 4844 happens all your old blobs will end up there too).",
